          <definition>
            <term>Heterogeneous mixture</term>
            <meaning>
              <para>A heterogeneous mixture is one that consists of two or more substances. It is non-uniform and the different components of the mixture can be seen.</para>
            </meaning>
          </definition>
          <para>Heterogeneous mixtures can be further subdivided according to whether it is two liquids mixed, a solid and a liquid or a liquid and a gas or even a gas and a solid. These mixtures are given special names which you can see in table below.</para>
